model.hand.analyzer

Class OmahaAnalyzer

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.hand.analyzer.HandAnalyzer
      • model.hand.analyzer.OmahaAnalyzer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HandAnalyzerInterface

    public class OmahaAnalyzer
extends HandAnalyzer
    An implementation of HandAnalyzer used to analyze Omaha hands.

    This implementation analyzes nine card Omaha hands following the rules of Omaha. The best hand a player can have must contain two card's from the player's hand and three from the community cards.

    Since:
    9/26/16
    Version:

    • Method Detail

      • fiveCardCombinations

        public final java.util.List<java.util.List<Card>> fiveCardCombinations(java.util.List<Card> fullHand)
        The list of all the five Card hands in fullHand.

        This method is optional when implementing this interface.

        This implementation breaks the full nine card final Omaha hand into its 5 card combinations by the rules of Omaha poker, two cards must be from the player's hand, and three must be community cards.
        Parameters:
        fullHand - the full list of cards to analyze
        Returns:
        all the five card hand combinations
